TextBlock.TextLine: P. next as to the concernes of mr. Peeters I'll writte to him this day the needful
& if the goods must be sold, I am of opinion, that they will not yeald much
above the halfe of their cost, so that £10 a 12 will signifie nothing
I could wish with all my heart thes poore clothing had their mony & that
I was cleare of that concernes whilst I remaine with kindesaeut
In Antwarp 28 maij 1681
London Abram vivian
th
S. mij last to you was on the 24: curitt with a remise for £375 on m.
Andre panieer in London for my acctt. which I hope is come to yd handes now
th
have before mee yd of 13: curitt above sand remise will be a sufficient
assistance towards what you have to pay, and as soone as possible shall
remitt more for yd acctt: I am glad that mr. skiner is better, I hope
there shall be no neglect to send by this first vessel 50 bayes & 3 bales
of cloth, and when any mare packes of cloth come to hull lett 203
be sent for Rotterd am to my order butt in non, butt english or hallants
vessels: I thinck I ordered more then 50 bayes where fore in case the
rest be not bought yett lett itt be of I& R.K. thought you should
imploy John Holroid to itt, & thought all our bayes were bought
& that wee have non of that sort, you may order m. Holroide to provide
40 more of 1e RK the best I can Cett: you must advise mee how
the price of kersies is now in the north, for I beleave wee shall want
more then 150 peeces in ordered & wee ought to have them here att
the beginiing of July, or att least part of them
as for the laces the norrow sort I finde to content, butt the crawint
or broadest sorts I finde butt very few, because they do not make
them altoghether so, where fore have ordered some to be made whist
I'll endeavour all I can to finish one packett this week, butt can
send no Antwarp laces, till I see a pattarne, or know what ground itt
is I lony to have yd advise of what passes, for I would faine have goods
from the north as soone as others & not be lest in arrieve which pray
minde, whilst I remaine with kinde solurs
In Antwerp 28 maij 1681
th
London Pickering & Robinson
msssr. my last to you was on the 20: curitt sence recy of 13 ditto where
bj revoyce to see yd safe returne from the north where I observe you have
don what I could reguire, so hope the goods will prove according god sending
them safe over shall be able to iudge how they will prove & proceed if
in corridged: I hope they shall come with the first vessel now in londing
as you promise butt if either of the packes should come tolave
itt might besent for Rotterdam consyned to my order, thought I rather
had them to come with the first vessel now for ostend: pray lett
lare betaken that they be shipt aboard an English or hollands vessel
because the brandenbough caperd are out op on the spanards, which
causes somes alteration here I do exspect advise of the goods
seeng shipt as also patt & rest with kinde salues
I shall send yd bales of tykes to brugges to be ships
aboard an Englisl vessel which will come there first
because of the copers a bove
In Antwerpen 28 Maij 1681
Leuven Joan De Goede
mons. in antwoort aenden ul van 21 deser hebbe voor het bewijs mij gesonden ontf
een hondert en vijf guldens ende mijne restet geene noch moet hebben 2 xb
lest leden exclus is ontrent ƒ420: 1 ½ soo ul dat kan effenen sal mij groote
vrintschap geschiden dat accordeert niet met ul noticie mij gesonden, maer
daer en sijn veel erreuren, want ul creditteert mij niet volgens de perticulier
rekeninge dewelke ick aen ul heb gesonden dewelke gelieft te examineeren
ende ul wel een generale rekeninge senden waermede groet
ul scrijft van stalen t'senden vermidts de menighte te groot is
ende die ul souden aenstaen, soude ick ondertusschen vergeten me te senden
soo dat is niet de doen als bijt geschigt vand'ooge want sortering
genogh hebben
ee
In Antwerpen 28 maij 1681
Brugge Rap: Coots -
mr. sedert mijnen Jonghst van 26 deser den ul van selve dato bekomen sien
de cattoene lijnwaeten heden tegemoet denk dat ul aen f: Herrebout de
noodigh ordre sal hebbe gesondenen a de gesonde Rek sal nae sien & daccorte
bevindende ul voor creditteeren, niet tegenstaende ul schrijft dat de vrind
in England tijdelijk vande branden boughers comissie vaders gewaert schadt is
ben seer voor lamere beducht omdes will dat de brieven van leesten vrijdag
uyt london daer geen mentie van make & buyten twijffel soo geen perticul
advis de binlanders is tegen gesonden de selve al sullen sijn vertroken
is & daer geen weterstaen omde capers te verdrijven wat passeert sien met
In Antwerpen 28 meij 1681
impasientie te gemoet
Brussel Stephanus Kints -
monsr. volgens mijn noticie soo had ul mij belast, dat ontrent desen tijt van noch
drij hondert guldens soude disponeren, d welk heden gedaen hebben te betalen aen
mons. Joseph Sabberton, over sulx versoeke mijnen brief gelieft te vereeren, ist aenstont
niet gelegen, ul kan het tot saturdagh uyt stellen: ben tegenwordigh seer wel versien
van alle soorten van engelsche goederen soo ul iets noodigh hebt gelieft te commanderen
28 maij 1681
Brussel Joseph Sabberton Ith
Sr. I wrott to you the 26: curitt: what was needfull, now beleave mee I could findes
no bill for Brussels to my accommodetion, where fore am forceed to t roubled you
with mj owne, on tenhanus kints about the gersemert forthree hand hounered guild
which I doubt not, butt he will pay punctually shall send you a saturday on
other, whilst I hope that you finde my desired lacces to content, of which
exspect yd advise whilst I remaine with kinde saluto
28 maij 1681
Brussel Peeters
messr. sedert dat aen ul 14 deser heb geschreven geen van ul vernomen hebbe
nu largo scrijven van monsr. slaughter den welken in geender hande maniere
en wil te doen hebben de goederen wederom te nemen, maer verstaet gelt
te hebben int geheel, ende sigh te houden aen het accort in ul vertreck hem
toegestaen, oversulx pressent mij dat men de goederen bij the nick of the candle
soude verkoopen, soo dat hier in confus ben, oversulx gelieft daer
in te voor sien ende wart mogelijk tot de resterende pertije
gelt te fourneiren ick sal gelijk ul hebbe geseijt daertoe provideeren
tgeene goet comt op ul rekeninge ofte daer ontrent terwijlen
ul advies af waghtende & naer groet blijve.
